<subSubSection id="C35678CBFF93FF87FF25F8EA604BADF2" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF93FF86FF25F8EA66F4A8F2" blockId="2.[151,1436,1901,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF93FF86FF25F8EA623CA886" bold="true" box="[201,340,1901,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="54F795E2FF93FF86FE8BF8E962A7A886" box="[359,463,1902,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Holotype</typeStatus>
male, previously preserved in alcohol; specimen somewhat discolored by alcohol action. Body length 2.6 mm; wing length 3.9 mm. Frons shining black, wider than anterior ocellus width. Face slightly narrower than frons, approximately as wide as anterior ocellus width. Ocellar tubercle slightly protuberant with 
<number id="3D843967FF93FF86FF3DF85D63B7A8F2" box="[209,223,2010,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of ocellar setae. Postcranium black, gray pruinose. Antenna yellow, flagellum with one flagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF92FF87FF7BFF1061C0AD3F" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Proboscis yellow. Palpus yellowish. Thorax shining black, gray pruinose; postpronotal and postalar lobes slightly yellow. Thoracic setae: 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FE49FF3B62DBAFD4" box="[421,435,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
antepronotals; 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FD8FFF3B61E5AFD4" box="[611,653,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
minute proepisternals; 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FC75FF3B60ACAFD4" box="[921,964,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
katatergitals; other setae as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C50C3FF92FF87FF7BFF676272AFF8" box="[151,282,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipennis">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF92FF87FF7BFF676272AFF8" box="[151,282,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">limbipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (diagnosed above). Legs shining yellow with mid and hind coxae, hind tibia and all tarsi slightly darker. Femora/tibiae setae slightly stronger: mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FC9DFE8360DEAE1C" box="[881,950,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FC4BFE8360DEAE1C" box="[935,950,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FBEFFE836779AE1C" box="[1027,1041,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
anterodorsal, 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FB59FE8367ABAE1C" box="[1205,1219,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
posterodorsal near middle, 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FF1EFEA06274AE3F" box="[242,284,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
ventral along distal half; hind femur (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FD28FEA0606EAE3F" box="[708,774,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FD14FEA0606EAE3F" box="[760,774,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FCA2FEA06034AE3F" box="[846,860,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
anteroventral at distal third; hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FAF4FEA06632AE3F" box="[1304,1370,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FAA0FEA06632AE3F" box="[1356,1370,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FF7BFECB63A8AE64" box="[151,192,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
slender dorsal setae. 
<collectingCountry id="F35B6BD0FF92FF87FE54FECB6298AE64" box="[440,496,332,356]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsomere 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FD9CFECB6116AE64" box="[624,638,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
with one longer dorsal seta. Fore tarsus (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FBB5FECB67F3AE64" box="[1113,1179,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FB63FECB67F3AE64" box="[1167,1179,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) unicolorous with tarsomere 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FF02FEE86394AE87" box="[238,252,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
, swollen dorsally. Wing (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FDF7FEE86136AE87" box="[539,606,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FDA3FEE86136AE87" box="[591,606,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) entirely hyaline with inconspicuous pterostigma. Cell dm truncate. Veins M 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FF5CFE2463D0AEB1" box="[176,184,419,433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
, M 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FF33FE24638FAEB1" box="[223,231,419,433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FEDFFE246253AEB1" box="[307,315,419,433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
evanescent. Halter white. Abdomen shining black, more gray pruinose on terminalia. Sternites 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FA9EFE1366F3AEAC" box="[1394,1435,404,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
slightly yellow. Tergite 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FE73FE3D62C5AED2" box="[415,429,442,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FE57FE3D6295AED2" box="[443,509,442,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FE03FE3D6295AED2" box="[495,509,442,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) with distal sinus. Epandrium (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FCB7FE3D60F6AED2" box="[859,926,442,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FC63FE3D60F6AED2" box="[911,926,442,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes of same height with shallow sinus. Anterior cercus very large with internal sinus; posterior cercus somewhat short; median lobe membranous with long setae. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FCCEFD856000AD1A" box="[802,872,514,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FCB5FD856000AD1A" box="[857,872,514,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) with setae medially and apex somewhat simple. Ejaculatory apodeme with short dorsal lamella.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF92FF87FF25FDCD600DADCF" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Female. Body length not measured; wing length 2.4 mm. Frons and face as in male. Fore tarsomere 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FAF3FDCD6645AD62" box="[1311,1325,586,610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
not swollen. 
<collectingCountry id="F35B6BD0FF92FF87FF2BFDE86397AD87" box="[199,255,623,647]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur without anteroventral setae. 
<collectingCountry id="F35B6BD0FF92FF87FD60FDE861ACAD87" box="[652,708,623,647]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FCD0FDE86022AD87" box="[828,842,623,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
dorsal setae. Tergite 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FBDBFDE8672DAD87" box="[1079,1093,623,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FBB8FDE867D6AD87" box="[1108,1214,623,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FB7FFDE867D6AD87" box="[1171,1214,623,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
</figureCitation>
) with distinct distal sulcus. Sternite 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FEA7FD156231ADAA" box="[331,345,658,682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FE86FD15628EADAA" box="[362,486,658,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FE47FD15628EADAA" box="[427,486,658,682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.1">8, 10</number>
</figureCitation>
) highly modified, with distinct sulcus ventrally and laterally. Genital fork (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF92FF87FAAEFD1566FBADAA" box="[1346,1427,658,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF92FF87FA94FD1566FBADAA" box="[1400,1427,658,682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) small with apex short U–shaped. Genital chamber membranous.
</paragraph>
